Moving columns
  record a macro - `qa` to start and `q` to end
  repeat macro - `@@`
  or use macro - `@a`

Sort on given column
  see what column you're in using bottom right
  use this link to help:
  https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1355004/how-to-sort-numeric-and-literal-columns-in-vim

Jump around
	go to newer position in CHANGE list - `g,`
  * go to older position in CHANGE list - `g;`
	go to newer position in JUMP list - `Ctrl + i`
  *	go to older position in JUMP list - `Ctrl + o`
    go to parenthesis with - `%`


Yank
	Yank relative line above you with `:-yXX` (xx being the relative line number)
	Yank relative line below you with `:+yXX` (xx being the relative line number)


Find
	find / -path "/mnt" -prune -o -perm /u+s,g+s,o+t 2>/dev/null -exec ls -ld {} \;
	ls -d /[^m]* | xargs -I % zsh -c 'ls -ld  %/**/*' 2>/dev/null | egrep "(^...s.*)|(^......s.*)"
	https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4210042/how-do-i-exclude-a-directory-when-using-find
	

Copy/Paste
	From system clipboard to terminal emulator -> shift+ins (insert is Fn+v)
	From TE to system -> tmux copy mode is setup to auto add to clipboard
